args:
As Cleo treats the temporarily revived Alberius
to a meal, he explains there is nothing wrong
with Cleo feeling lost. After their brief chance
encounter, Alberius vanishes. Having braved
three farewells with her beloved king, Cleo
solidifies her resolve once more.
Something similar to this happened back\non the snowy mountain...
See here, spirit! I'll not be deceived!\nYou are but an illusion of His Majesty!
And yet...the power and warmth of your\nmana. None but he could lay claim to\nits like.
Why do you laugh, spirit?! If you attempt\nanything untoward, I shall be hasty inâ€”
The cautious side of you remains\nunchanged.

But despite your concern regarding what
you see before you, you stand firm and on
guard, with confidence in your eyes.
You have grown stronger.
I don't understand it myself, but I know I\nam not false, at any rate.
It has been some years, Cleo.
I shall cry if I wish it! I've wanted to see\nyou again for an age...
My apologies. I did not have the luxury of\ntime back in the binding ruins.
And after three hundred years, I stood\nbefore you as you suffered, unable to act!
I see I have been a cause of some worry.\nBut as you can see, I am well enough.
It does not seem as though much time has\npassed since that day, but I still wonder...\nwhere is this place?
Events have conspired such to bring us to\nNorth Grastaea, and we are at the Sacred\nTree in the north of the Faerie Kingdom.
The Sacred Tree? Ah, that takes me back.\nI stopped here once when I was on my way\nto learn the faeries' secret arts.
The fact I stand before you now is a\nmiracle attributable to this tree.
Has the Sacred Tree returned you to life?
I don't profess a deep understanding of\nwhat is happening here, but that should\nserve well enough for an explanation.
Judging from the way I feel, it seems as\nthough I am a projection of consciousness.
We have a friend traveling with us who has\nprojected herself here from another world.
This may be similar. But in my case,\nI will not be able to remain for long.
The dead become mana once more.
Right now, I do no more than force my way\nceaselessly against that current.
Oh, but this is terrible. We're finally\nreunited, and yet...
I have something to ask of you, Cleo,\nif you will hear it.
I am ever your loyal servant, Your Majesty.
If there is anything I can do for you,\nyou have but to give the word.
Very well. I would have you make a meal.
A meal? That's all? Er, I mean, I would be\nmore than happy to!
Good. Oh, and as you cook, tell me of the\njourneys that led you to this place.
Of course! Just let me get my supplies!
Delicious. It has been an age since I was\nable to enjoy your excellent cooking.
I did not know if this body could consume\nsustenance, but I am glad to find it was\nnot an issue. Thank you, Cleo.
You need not thank me, Majesty! I am\nonly sorry to offer you such simple fare.
Had I know you would be gracing me with\nyour presence, I would have procured more\nextravagant ingredients.
Say no more. This is exactly what I was\nhoping to eat.
I'm still not convinced this is not a dream.
I must say, it is quite the set of\ncircumstances that brought you here\nto the Faerie Kingdom.
Indeed, each day seems to pass in a more\ndizzying fashion than the last.
I am glad to hear that you seem satisfied,\nthough. In truth, I worried a great deal\nabout leaving you in the Halidom.
It is an honor beyond all measure that you\nmight worry for me in such a way.
Yet I am nothing but hesitation and\naimless motion, and do not deserve such.
The prince does not share your blood...
I know full well that I don't need to be\nconcerned with something like that,\nand yet no matter what I do...
Can I truly continue on this journey with\nmy mind so lost, Your Majesty?
I can only offer guidance in the form of\nthese words, Cleo...
It is no crime to feel adrift on stormy seas.\nIndeed, this serves as proof that you face\nmatters with all due seriousness.
It means you are attempting to bear a\nheavy burden yourself.
So long as you cannot predict the\nfuture, it is only natural to worry when\nmaking a weighty decision.
Did I make the right choice here?\nShould I have acted differently there?
Though we worry over those things, we can\nonly continue on the path we have chosen\nand believe.
While we cannot know which path is true,\nwe can make true the path we choose.
Did you worry over such things yourself?\nYou always seemed to so easily make the\nright decisions.
I merely took efforts to make it appear so.\nThat makes me seem cooler, no?
No, Your Majesty! This is too soon!
Unfortunately, I have no power over the\nrelentless flow of time.
We're never going to be able to see\neach other again...
Then let us part with smiles.
When I left the Halidom for the binding\nruins, ours was an unwilling farewellâ€”\njust as it was three centuries later.
This time, let us do things differently.
Hear me, Cleo. Protecting everyone?\nFighting the Other?
I did those things because I wanted to,\nnot out of some grandiose philosophy or\nthe luck of my parentage.
I simply balked at the idea of the world\nbecoming a place where I couldn't enjoy\nyour wonderful cooking.
I didn't want someone else to do it for me.
In that same vein, you should just do what\nyou are capable of doing. That is my final\npiece of advice to you.
Your counsel is as wise as ever.
It has been the honor of my life to serve\nyou, Majesty.
Did I manage a proper send-off this time?
Still, how can he expect me to part with\na smile when I...I... *sob*
Where am I...? What did... Ah!
I saw His Majesty! But was it all a dream?
Thank you so much, Your Majesty.
Ho there, Cleo. You're up early.
Good morning, Gatov. I thought I'd whip up\nsomething special for breakfast to help\neveryone regain their strength.
It seems you had a late night.
Yes, and an eventful one. But I'm all\nrightâ€”truly I am.
Sounds like you dealt with your doubts.
Yes, I think so, at least somewhat.
This is a damn fine breakfast, Cleo!
I thought I smelled something. What have\nwe done to deserve such a feast?
I am just trying to get everyone motivated\nso you can be at your best.
You always take such good care of us,\nCleo. Thank you.
Oh, er, nothing. Now then, everything will\nbe ready shortly, so grab a plate!
Once we're done eating, we'll head out.
